<div class="hello">
  <h2>TUTORIAL ON HOW TO MAKE PASTA ALLA CARBONARA CAUSE I'M LOWKEY HUNGRY</h2>
  <p>Warning: this is not for the faint of heart.</p>
</div>
<p>
To prepare spaghetti alla carbonara, start by placing a pot of salted water on the stove to cook the pasta. Meanwhile, remove the rind from the guanciale and cut it first into slices (1) and then into strips about 1cm thick (2, 3). The leftover rind can be reused to flavor other dishes.
</p>

<img src="https://ricette.giallozafferano.it/images/ricette/244/24489/24489_draft-spaghetti-alla-carbonara_strip_1-3.jpg" alt="carbonara123">
<p>
Pour the pieces of guanciale into a non-stick pan (4) and saut√© for about 10 minutes over medium-high heat, being careful not to burn it, as this would release too strong a flavor. Meanwhile, drop the spaghetti into the boiling water (5) and cook them al dente. In the meantime, pour the egg yolks into a bowl (6).
</p

<img src="https://ricette.giallozafferano.it/images/ricette/244/24489/24489_draft-spaghetti-alla-carbonara_strip_4-6.jpg" alt="carbonara456">

